-- U.S. Fed awards $40.72 bln reverse repos Tuesday
-- 
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 01:31PM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Dec 16 (Reuters) - The U.S. Federal Reserve on Tuesday awarded $40.72 billion of overnight fixed-rate reverse repurchase agreements to 29 bidders at an interest rate of 0.05 percent, the New York Federal Reserve said on its website.

On Monday, the U.S. central bank allotted $34.59 billion in overnight reverse repos (RRP) to 26 bidders, including Wall Street dealers, money market mutual funds and mortgage finance agencies at an interest rate of 0.05 percent.